-- Source: entities/persons/paulao-muzenza.sql (NEW)
-- ============================================================
-- GENEALOGY PERSON: Paulão (Muzenza)
-- Generated: 2026-01-10
-- ============================================================
-- Mestre Paulão is the founder of Grupo Muzenza de Capoeira (1972),
-- one of the largest capoeira organizations in the world. Born in
-- Rio de Janeiro, he was trained by his brother Mestre Mintirinha.
-- After establishing Muzenza, he stepped back in 1978 to pursue a
-- 31-year military career in the Brazilian Navy, allowing his student
-- Mestre Burguês to expand the group internationally.
-- ============================================================
--
-- BIRTH DATE: June 16, 1955 (confirmed by IPHAN official registry)
-- BIRTH PLACE: Rio de Janeiro, RJ, Brazil (Sampaio neighborhood)
--
-- TEACHERS:
-- - Mestre Mintirinha (Luiz Américo da Silva) - his older brother,
--   whom Paulão considers his "first and only master"
-- - Started training at age 8 in the 1960s on Rua Ozéas Mota
-- - Later trained at Milton Ribeiro gymnasium in Olaria
-- - Trained at Club Santo Antônio de Ramos
--
-- LINEAGE (via Mintirinha):
-- Mestre Paraná (Oswaldo Lisboa dos Santos) → Mestre Mintirinha → Mestre Paulão
--
